body:
I also changed the API for `BuoyancyForce` so that the "formulation" is a positional argument. I think this is nicer esp because there is no sensible default and it is central to `BuoyancyForce` and required.

I also changed the property of `BuoyancyForce.model` to `BuoyancyForce.formulation`. This avoids the name conflict with `NonhydrostaticModel` etc, which leads to very silly and confusing constructions like `model.buoyancy.model.gravity_unit_vector`. Now this will be `model.buoyancy.formulation.gravity_unit_vector`.

@tomchor you may want to take a look.
